The paper deals with visual recognition tasks and machine learning, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of unsupervised learning and the focus on feature learning suggest that the paper could also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on image datasets, which could also make it relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
